section.section:
The notice shall:
State that the vehicle has been taken into custody;
Describe the year, make, model, and vehicle identification number of the vehicle;
Give the location of the facility where the vehicle is held;
Inform the owner and secured party of the owner's and secured party's right to reclaim the vehicle within 11 working days after the date of the notice, on payment of all towing, recovery, and storage charges owed to the automotive dismantler and recycler or scrap processor resulting from taking or holding the vehicle; and
State that the failure of the owner or secured party to exercise this right in the time provided is:
A waiver by the owner or secured party of all of the owner's or secured party's right, title, and interest in the vehicle; and
A consent to the dismantling, destroying, or scrapping of the vehicle.

text.section:
In addition to documentation of notice under subsections (b) and (c) of this section, an automotive dismantler and recycler or scrap processor shall obtain from a person who provides the vehicle:
An affidavit in a form approved by the Administration signed under penalty of perjury by the person providing the vehicle;
A copy of the driver's license of the person who provides the vehicle;
Any proof of ownership documents acceptable to the Administration, if available; and
If the vehicle is transported by a tow vehicle, a copy of the registration of the tow vehicle.

An affidavit under subsection (d) of this section shall include:
A statement that the person providing the vehicle has the lawful right to possess the vehicle and the basis of that right;
A statement that, except as provided in § 25-209 of this article, the vehicle may not be retitled and may only be dismantled, destroyed, or scrapped;
A description of the vehicle, including year, make, model, color, and vehicle identification number;
The name, address, driver's license number, and signature of the person providing the vehicle;
An acknowledgement that:
The form is being signed under penalty of perjury; and
The penalties established under § 27-101.2 of this article apply;
The date the vehicle is provided to the automotive dismantler and recycler or scrap processor;
The name, address, and State-issued license number of the automotive dismantler and recycler or scrap processor acquiring the vehicle; and
The printed name, title, and signature of the person accepting the vehicle.
